# Breadboard Robot

The files herein are intended to support two different modes of running the breadboard robot

## Remote Control
rc_robot_main.py - This program uses BluetoothClient and Buzzer library classes. The idea is to walk students through
developing this a step at a time. It uses callbacks to support students who don't know OOP. It certainly would be possible
to add a subclass strategy for those that do

## Autonomous Robot Control
robot.py - Robot class that can be programmed by a student, as opposed to being controlled by remote control.  Eventually the plan is to 
add the capability to switch between RC and autonomous modes (See Robot project)

## Uses
- BLEClient
- Buzzer
- Servo (optional)

